Actividad Módulo 29: Introducción al Clustering¶

  • Importacin de un modelo con datos de tarjetas de crdito (cc general.csv)
  • EDA completo siguiento los modelos anteriores
  • Feature engineering - estandarizacin, eliminacin, nuevas columnas
  • Uso del algortmo K-Means: elbow plot y anlisis
  • Visualizacin de los resultados del modelo de clustering: bar plots y clases - identificacin y perfilamiento de clases
  • Dendogramas y validacin de la calidad del fit
  • Silhouette score
  • Visualizacin simple de los resultados del modelo de clustering
  • Interpretacin final de resultados de los clusters generados por el modelo

CSV CC GENERAL.csv¶

  • CUST_ID : Identification of Credit Card holder (Categorical)
  • BALANCE : Balance amount left in their account to make purchases
  • BALANCE_FREQUENCY : How frequently the Balance is updated, score between 0 and 1 (1 = frequently updated, 0 = not frequently updated)
  • PURCHASES : Amount of purchases made from account
  • ONEOFF_PURCHASES : Maximum purchase amount done in one-go
  • INSTALLMENTS_PURCHASES : Amount of purchase done in installment
  • CASH_ADVANCE : Cash in advance given by the user
  • PURCHASES_FREQUENCY : How frequently the Purchases are being made, score between 0 and 1 (1 = frequently purchased, 0 = not frequently purchased)
  • ONEOFFPURCHASESFREQUENCY : How frequently Purchases are happening in one-go (1 = frequently purchased, 0 = not frequently purchased)
  • PURCHASESINSTALLMENTSFREQUENCY : How frequently purchases in installments are being done (1 = frequently done, 0 = not frequently done)
  • CASHADVANCEFREQUENCY : How frequently the cash in advance being paid
  • CASHADVANCETRX : Number of Transactions made with "Cash in Advanced"
  • PURCHASES_TRX : Numbe of purchase transactions made
  • CREDIT_LIMIT : Limit of Credit Card for user
  • PAYMENTS : Amount of Payment done by user
  • MINIMUM_PAYMENTS : Minimum amount of payments made by user
  • PRCFULLPAYMENT : Percent of full payment paid by user
  • TENURE : Tenure of credit card service for user

Eliminación de columnas¶

df2 = df.copy()

# Eliminacin de variables no necesarias
df2.drop(columns='CUST_ID', inplace=True)

# Elimincacin de variables con alta correlacin
df2.drop(columns=['PURCHASES', 'PURCHASES_INSTALLMENTS_FREQUENCY', 'CASH_ADVANCE_FREQUENCY'], inplace=True)

Normalización de columnas¶

  • Balance
  • Balance frequency (negative)
  • One off purchases
  • Installments purchases
  • Cash advance
  • Purchases Frequency (both)
  • One off purchases frequency
  • Cash advance trx
  • Purchases trx
  • Credit Limit
  • Payments
  • Minimum payments
  • PRC full payment
  • Tenure (negative)

# Transform skewness with natural logarithm
df2['BALANCE_norm'] = np.log(df['BALANCE'] + 1)
df2['BALANCE_FREQUENCY_norm'] = np.log(df['BALANCE_FREQUENCY'] + 1)
df2['ONEOFF_PURCHASES_norm'] = np.log(df['ONEOFF_PURCHASES'] + 1)
df2['INSTALLMENTS_PURCHASES_norm'] = np.log(df['INSTALLMENTS_PURCHASES'] + 1)
df2['CASH_ADVANCE_norm'] = np.log(df['CASH_ADVANCE'] + 1)
df2['PURCHASES_FREQUENCY_norm'] = np.log(df['PURCHASES_FREQUENCY'] + 1)
df2['ONEOFF_PURCHASES_FREQUENCY_norm'] = np.log(df['ONEOFF_PURCHASES_FREQUENCY'] + 1)
df2['CASH_ADVANCE_TRX_norm'] = np.log(df['CASH_ADVANCE_TRX'] + 1)
df2['PURCHASES_TRX'] = np.log(df['CASH_ADVANCE_TRX'] + 1)
df2['CREDIT_LIMIT_norm'] = np.log(df['CREDIT_LIMIT'] + 1)
df2['PAYMENTS_norm'] = np.log(df['PAYMENTS'] + 1)
df2['MINIMUM_PAYMENTS_norm'] = np.log(df['MINIMUM_PAYMENTS'] + 1)
df2['PRC_FULL_PAYMENT_norm'] = np.log(df['PRC_FULL_PAYMENT'] + 1)
df2['TENURE_norm'] = np.log(df['TENURE'] + 1)

In [ ]:
from scipy.spatial.distance import cdist
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
mean_distortions = []

clusters = range(1,20)

for k in clusters:
    model = KMeans(n_clusters=k, n_init='auto')
    model.fit(df3)
    prediction = model.predict(df3)

    mean_distortions.append(sum(np.min(cdist(df3, model.cluster_centers_, 'euclidean'), axis=1)) / df3.shape[0])

# Plot Scree Graph
plt.plot(clusters, mean_distortions, 'bx-')
plt.xlabel('k - # Clusters')
plt.ylabel('Distorsin Promedio')
plt.title('Resultados KMeans')

In [ ]:
# Silhouette score
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score

sil_df = pd.DataFrame({}, columns=['Model', 'n_clusters', 'Score'])

for n_clusters in range(2,20):
    clusterer = KMeans(n_clusters=n_clusters, random_state=1, n_init='auto')
    predictions = clusterer.fit_predict(df3)
    centers = clusterer.cluster_centers_

    score = silhouette_score(df3, clusterer.labels_, metric='euclidean')
    
    # Add score to sil_df
    sil_df = pd.concat(objs=[sil_df, pd.DataFrame([['KMeans', n_clusters, score]], columns=['Model', 'n_clusters', 'Score'])])

Insights:¶

En el primer grfico se ve como el grupo 0 predomina en valores altos de ONEOFF_PURCHASES_FREQUENCY_norm, mientras que los otros dos grupos se mezclan ms en valores pequeos de dicha variable. En el segundo grfico se puede ver como el grupo 2 predocumna en valores bajos de la variable PAYMENTS_norm mientras que el grupo 0 predomina en valores altos de ambas variables graficadas
  • En un inicio el grfico de codo sirvi para hacer un primer anlisis donde se escogi dividir la muestra en 8 clusters, sin embargo, al realizar el diagrama de Silhouette Score contra el nmero de clusters, se puede ver que el nmero ptimo de clusters es 3 por lo que se hicieron las correcciones al modelo y se reinterpretaron los resultados en cada seccin de insights
